            <titleabbrev>SOLOR</titleabbrev>
            <para> According to most sources, Rx is derived from the Latin word “recipe,” meaning
                “take.” Among several alternative theories, however, is the belief that the Rx
                symbol evolved from the Eye of Horus, an ancient Egyptian symbol associated with
                healing powers. </para>
            <para> It is generally thought that it has medieval roots as an abbreviation for a form
                of the Late Latin word “recipere” meaning “to take.” </para>
            <para> compositio, conpositio, praescriptum, recipe </para>
